---
import { base } from '../utils/base';
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="The story behind Be Ready Beaumont and our K-12 approach to career readiness.">
  <section class="bg-brand-navy text-white py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black">About Be Ready Beaumont</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-white/70 max-w-2xl">
        A K-12 Career Technical Education program that starts with self-discovery
        and ends with students who know who they are and where they're going.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="space-y-8 text-brand-slate/80 leading-relaxed">
        <p class="text-lg">
          Be Ready Beaumont began in 2017 with a simple belief: when students connect who they are
          to a career that capitalizes on their strengths, interests, and values, they don't just
          find a job — they find purpose.
        </p>

        <p>
          Beaumont Unified School District knows there's no one-size-fits-all path. College is a
          great opportunity for many, but it doesn't always provide every student with the skills
          to pursue a career they're passionate about. The economy has shifted from degrees to skills —
          critical thinking, collaboration, innovation, continuous learning. Be Ready Beaumont was
          built for this reality.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brand-navy pt-4">It Starts Early</h2>

        <p>
          In elementary school, students explore who they are and what interests them through the
          <strong>Pathful</strong> platform — age-appropriate assessments and activities that promote
          self-discovery and career awareness. In upper elementary, <strong>Holland's RIASEC
          occupational themes</strong> are introduced, helping students understand how their
          strengths, interests, and values connect to real careers.
        </p>

        <p>
          By middle school, students enter dedicated CTE courses — Robotics, Product Innovation
          and Design, Digital Media, Performing Arts — with medical programs expanding to every
          middle school site.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brand-navy pt-4">12 Pathways, 7 Sectors</h2>

        <p>
          At the high school level, students choose from 12 CTE pathways across six industry sectors
          at Beaumont and Glen View High Schools. Every pathway is taught by an instructor with
          real industry experience. Every pathway connects to post-secondary opportunities through
          dual enrollment and articulated courses with Mt. San Jacinto College.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brand-navy pt-4">Institutional Commitment</h2>

        <p>
          The Beaumont USD Board of Trustees didn't just approve CTE — they invested in it. Before
          the 2021-22 school year, the Board adopted a CTE teacher salary schedule that recognizes
          industry experience (without requiring a bachelor's degree) and absorbed all CTE teaching
          positions into the general fund. That's not a pilot program — that's a permanent commitment.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-brand-light rounded-2xl p-8 my-8">
          <blockquote class="text-lg italic text-brand-slate/90">
            "Be Ready Beaumont is about supporting students in who they are as unique and amazing
            individuals, fueling their passion, and maximizing their opportunities for success.
            By focusing on skill development, personal reflection and growth, and expanding
            students' perspectives on post-secondary opportunities throughout their educational
            journey, we can help students find relevance in their learning and choose a career
            that gives them purpose."
          </blockquote>
          <cite class="block mt-4 font-bold text-brand-navy not-italic">Dr. Michael Breyer</cite>
          <span class="text-sm text-brand-slate/50">Director, College & Career Readiness</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Staff -->
      <div class="mt-16">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brand-navy mb-8">Leadership</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          {[
            {
              name: "Dr. Michael Breyer",
              title: "Director, College & Career Readiness",
              email: "mbreyer@beaumontusd.k12.ca.us",
            },
            {
              name: "Alicia Chamberlain",
              title: "TOSA, College & Career Readiness",
              email: "achamberlain@beaumontusd.k12.ca.us",
            },
            {
              name: "Eve Chester",
              title: "College & Career Readiness TOSA",
              email: "",
            },
            {
              name: "Susan Aguilar-Martinez",
              title: "Career Readiness Coordinator",
              email: "saguilarMartinez@beaumontusd.k12.ca.us",
            },
          ].map((person) => (
            <div class="bg-brand-light rounded-xl p-6">
              <p class="font-bold text-brand-navy">{person.name}</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-brand-slate/60">{person.title}</p>
              {person.email && (
                <a href={`mailto:${person.email}`} class="text-sm text-brand-blue hover:underline mt-1 inline-block">
                  {person.email}
                </a>
              )}
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
